r=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-100411-7}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|author=Arvind-Pal Singh Mandair|title=Sikhism: A Guide for the Perplexed|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vdhLAQAAQBAJ |year=2013|publisher=Bloomsbury Academic|isbn=978-1-4411-0231-7}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|first=Nikky-Guninder Kaur |last= Singh|title=Sikhism: An Introduction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h40AAwAAQBAJ|year= 2011|publisher=I. B. Tauris|isbn=978-0-85771-962-1}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|author=Henry Walker|editor=Kerry Brown|title=Sikh Art and Literature|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ddgO-DldmSwC|year=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-63136-0}}\n* {{cite journal | ref = harv | last = Bal | first = Sarjit Singh | title= Punjab After Independence (1947-1956) | journal= Proceedings of the Indian History Congress | year = 1985 | volume=46 |pages=416\u2013430 | jstor = 44141382 |pmid=22491937 }}\n* {{cite book | ref = harv | last = Doad | first = Karnail Singh | editor1-last = Si\u1e45gh | editor1-first = Harbans | title = Punjabi S\u016bb\u0101 Movement | date = 1997 | publisher = Punjab University, Patiala, 2011 | location = Patiala, Punjab, India |isbn=9788173803499 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/TheEncyclopediaOfSikhism-VolumeIiiM-r/page/n407 391]-404 | edition = 3rd | url = https://archive.org/details/TheEncyclopediaOfSikhism-VolumeIiiM-r | accessdate = 24 February 2020 | language = English}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons|Harmandir Sahib}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [http://sgpc.net/ Website of Shiromani Gurdwara Parbandhak Committee Official Website]\n\n{{Sikhism}}\n\n[[Category:1604 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Architecture of India]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Amritsar]]\n[[Category:Donations by Nizams of Hyderabad]]\n[[Category:Gurdwaras in Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Rebuilt buildings and structures in India]]\n[[Category:Religious buildings and structures completed in 1604]]\n[[Category:Religious buildings and structures 