{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Haiti", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Haiti}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Haiti\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Haiti]]\n| first_case      = [[Port-au-Prince]]\n| arrival_date    = 19 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=19|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = \n| recovery_cases  = 0\n| deaths          = 0\n| confirmed_cases = 15<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Eddyjalexis/status/1242893893844303872|title=Gen 8 ka #COVID19 konfime nan peyi a. #CIPC|author=Eddy Jackson Alexis|publisher=Twitter|date=25 March 2020|language=ht}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = 57\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Haiti]] in March 2020.\n\n==Timeline==\nOn 19 March, the first two cases in the country were confirmed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-haiti/haiti-declares-emergency-over-coronavirus-imposes-curfew-shuts-border-idUSKBN21700V |title=Haiti declares emergency over coronavirus, imposes curfew, shuts borders |work=Reuters |date=19 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320004855/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-haiti/haiti-declares-emergency-over-coronavirus-imposes-curfew-shuts-border-idUSKBN21700V |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Prevention==  \nOn 16 March, at midnight local time, Haiti's Prime Minister, [[Joseph Jouthe]], announced a two-week suspension of flights from Europe, Canada, the Dominican Republic, and Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus - Which countries have travel bans? |work=CNN |last=O'Hare |first=Maureen |last2=Hardingham |first2=Tamara |last-author-amp=y |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320091122/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[2020 in the Caribbean]]\n*[[Influx of disease in the Caribbean]]\n*[[HIV/AIDS in Latin America]]\n*[[2013\u20132014 chikungunya outbreak]]\n*[[2009 swine flu pandemic]]\n*[[2019\u20132020 dengue fever epidemic]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America]]\n*[[2010 Haiti earthquake]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{in lang|fr}} [https://mspp.gouv.ht/newsite/documentation.php?page=1&param1=valu1&param2=value2 Daily reports on Coronavirus pandemic] on mspp.gouv.ht\n* {{in lang|fr}} [https://mspp.gouv.ht/site/downloads/Plan%20de%20Pr%C3%A9paration%20et%20de%20R%C3%A9ponse%20du%20MSPP%20au%20CoronaVirus.pdf Plan of preparation and Respons MSPP against Coronavirus (March 2020)] on mspp.gouv.ht\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America}}\n{{#related:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Dominican Republic}}\n{{#related:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Haiti|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Haiti]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Caribbean|Haiti]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Haiti]]\n\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n{{Haiti-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Haiti}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic